  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dcf\u0d9b\u0dca\u200d\u0dba  \u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Investigations into the death of Mahesakhya Hasthiya",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forestry, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera yesterday (08) instructed the Secretary of the Ministry, Mrs. Chandra Herath, to initiate a formal investigation regarding the death of the Anuradhapura Mahesakhya elephant and the incident of cutting off the elephant's tusks when the elephant was on the verge of death and the non-action of the wildlife officials.",
        "Accordingly, the director general of wildlife has already submitted a complaint to the police in this regard and investigations are being conducted to find the person who cut the ivory using even official dogs.",
        "Also, the Director General of Wildlife informed the Minister that an investigation will be conducted by the Wildlife Department regarding the non-action of the wildlife officers until the elephant died and whether there has been any dereliction of duty by them."
      ],
